06.ROC curves of predictive classifiers

6.1 The ROC curves of three models with backward feature selection. The data of 915 samples (183 preterm pregnancies and 732 full-term pregnancies) was used developed predictive classifiers.

load("Preterm.RData")
SVM <- matrix(c(0,0,(1-0.870),0.885,1,1),3,2,byrow =T)
LDA <- matrix(c(0,0,(1-0.936),0.656,1,1),3,2,byrow =T)
LR <- matrix(c(0,0,(1-0.837),0.874,1,1),3,2,byrow =T)

plot(SVM,xlim=c(0,1),ylim=c(0,1),type="l",main="Backward",xlab="1-Specificity",ylab="Sensitivity",col="#DC0000B2",xaxs="i", yaxs="i",lwd=8,axes=F,cex.lab=2,cex.main=2)       
par(new=TRUE)
plot(LDA,type="l",main="",xlab="",ylab="",col="#00A087B2",xaxs="i", yaxs="i",lwd=8,axes=F)       
par(new=TRUE)
plot(LR,type="l",main="",xlab="",ylab="",col="#F39B7FB2",xaxs="i", yaxs="i",lwd=8,axes=F) 

axis(1,at=c(0,0.2,0.4,0.6,0.8,1),labels=c(0,20,40,60,80,100),cex.axis=2)
axis(2,at=c(0,0.2,0.4,0.6,0.8,1),labels=c(0,20,40,60,80,100),cex.axis=2)
box()
x1 <- c(0,1)
y1 <- c(0,1)
lines(x1,y1,lty=2)
legend(0.32,0.3,legend=c("SVM 0.878 (0.852-0.904)","LDA 0.796 (0.760-0.831)","LR 0.856 (0.828-0.883)"),fill=c("#DC0000B2","#00A087B2","#F39B7FB2"),cex=1.2,bty="n")

More details were showed in the manuscript.

6.3 The ROC curves of PTerm in Training, internal validation and two external validation cohorts.

Train <- matrix(c(0,0,(1-0.870),0.885,1,1),3,2,byrow =T)
V1 <- matrix(c(0,0,(1-0.867),0.823,1,1),3,2,byrow =T)
V2 <- matrix(c(0,0,(1-0.848),0.817,1,1),3,2,byrow =T)
V3 <- matrix(c(0,0,(1-0.806),0.817,1,1),3,2,byrow =T)
All <- matrix(c(0,0,(1-0.853),0.844,1,1),3,2,byrow =T)

plot(Train,xlim=c(0,1),ylim=c(0,1),type="l",main="PTerm",xlab="1-Specificity",ylab="Sensitivity",col="#DC0000B2",xaxs="i", yaxs="i",lwd=8,axes=FALSE,cex.lab=2,cex.main=2)       
par(new=TRUE)
plot(V1,type="l",main="",xlab="",ylab="",col="#00A087B2",xaxs="i", yaxs="i",lwd=8,axes=F)       
par(new=TRUE)
plot(V2,type="l",main="",xlab="",ylab="",col="#F39B7FB2",xaxs="i", yaxs="i",lwd=8,axes=F)       
par(new=TRUE)
plot(V3,type="l",main="",xlab="",ylab="",col="#FEE08B",xaxs="i", yaxs="i",lwd=8,axes=F) 
par(new=TRUE)
plot(All,type="l",main="",xlab="",ylab="",col="#3288BD",xaxs="i", yaxs="i",lwd=8,axes=F) 

axis(1,at=c(0,0.2,0.4,0.6,0.8,1),labels=c(0,20,40,60,80,100),cex.axis=2)
axis(2,at=c(0,0.2,0.4,0.6,0.8,1),labels=c(0,20,40,60,80,100),cex.axis=2)
box()
x1 <- c(0,1)
y1 <- c(0,1)
lines(x1,y1,lty=2)
legend(0.3,0.3,legend=c("Training 0.878 (0.852-0.904)","V1 0.845 (0.799-0.891)","V2 0.833 (0.802-0.853)","V3 0.812 (0.761-0.863)","All 0.849 (0.831-0.866)"),fill=c("#DC0000B2","#00A087B2","#F39B7FB2","#FEE08B","#3288BD"),cex=1.1,bty="n")

Train=train cohort; V1=internal validation cohort; V2=external cohort 1; V3 external cohort 2.
